To run configure, specify the machine type and the type of 
floating point numbers to use.

Examples:
./configure -cpu=dec float
./configure -cpu=sun double

Possible machine types (Unix versions) include: 
dec, ibm, hp, linux, sgi, solaris, sun
(sun is SUNOS, the predecessor to Solaris)

Possible number types are: 
float and double

double is the default.
